# Start Exploring the SmolNet

Want to start exploring the SmolNet, but haven't a clue where to start? This page is intended to help set you on the road!

We'll tell you what equipment you need, and point you at some useful search engines and other starting points.

!- TODO: Terminology (separate link) (gemspace, capsule, gemcap, gopherhole, glog, phlog, etc - be sure to differentiate between geminispace, and geminispace.org or whatever)

# Equipment

## Portals

If you're just testing the waters, then it's probably easiest to use your preferred web browser, together with a web portal that can translate between the Web and the SmolNet protocols (Gopher, Gemini, etc).

=> http://portal.mozz.us/ (Gemini, Spartan, Gopher...)
=> https://gopherproxy.meulie.net/ (Gopher only)
!- TODO: more portal links. Does geminiprotocol.net have some?

## Clients (Browsers... but not of the Web)

If you're done just walking around and perusing the SmolNet, and want to _soar_, here are some clients (browsers) that you can use for a more-immersive experience (and to give your portal's server a break!).

Advantages that a dedicated client provides over a portal, can (but don't
necessarily) include:
* Significantly faster load times
* Managing your login credentials (TLS-cert identities) in geminispace
* Subscribing to a capsule's updates
* The relief of knowing that so long as you stay in the client, that nasty Web can't harm you

My client-of-choice is Lagrange, which
* is available on multiple platforms,
* supports a large number of SmolNet protocols (including Gopher, Gemini, Titan, Spartan), but not Web protocols,
* can manage (and generate!) TLS-certificate identities for logging into capsules,
* can manage subscription feeds to any updates to favorite capsules,
* will generate a table of contents, for navigation convenience,
* generates a unique theme/appearance for each capsule,
* clearly distinguishes between SmolNet and Web hyperlinks, and
* uses (some) familiar keybindings from common web browsers

=> gemini://skyjake.fi/lagrange/ Lagrange (multiplatform)
=> https://github.com/MasterQ32/kristall Kristall (multiplatform; does Gemini, but not Gopher)
=> https://github.com/snoe/deedum Deedum (for Android; does Gemini, but not Gopher)
=> https://github.com/rkd77/elinks Elinks (In-terminal browser. Does Gemini,, does Gopher, does the Web too.)
